<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10150642>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Myrcianthes cruciata. A. Habit. B. Detail of the reddish bark exfoliating in irregular patches. C. Flowering branch. D. Buds and open flowers with tetramerous calyx. E. Fruits at different stages of maturity. F. Embryo. Vouchers: A, B) Proença et al. 5441, C) Farias et al. 307, E, F) Farias-Castro 2867. Photos: A, B) F.S.Dantas, C, D) M.C.V.Farias, E) A.S.Farias-Castro." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10150642/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10150644>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Morphological characters of Myrcianthes cruciata M.Ibrahim & Proença. A. Flowering branch. B. Inflorescence with old flowers. C. Leaf. D. Flower bud. E. Ovary in transversal section. F. Ovary in longitudinal section. G. Cotyledon after removal of the plumule.A–F from Farias et al. 307 (ASE, UB); G from Proença et al. 5441 (UB). Pen-and-ink illustration by Claudenir S. Caires." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10150644/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10150646>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Branch wood Anatomy of Myrcianthes cruciata M.Ibrahim & Proença. A–B; M. Transverse section. C–D, I. Tangential section. E;J; K–L. Radial section. F–G. Macerate with vascular tracheids (arrows). H. Simple perforation plate; I. Intervessel pit. J. Vesselray pits. K. Fibre with distinctly bordered pits (arrow); L. Disjunctive ray cells (arrows); M. tyloses in vessels. Bars 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10150646/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

